%N A287876 Numbers in Hebrew that do not contain the letter "Ayin".
%C A287876 Suggested by the "Eban numbers", A006933, and, inspired by that name, could also be called the "Eyes shut" sequence, since ayin also means "eye" in Hebrew.
%C A287876 If the OEIS permitted non-ASCII characters, another name would be the עban numbers.
%H A287876 Amiram Eldar, <a href="/A287876/b287876.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%t A287876 q[k_] := !StringContainsQ[IntegerName[k, "Hebrew"], FromCharacterCode[1506]]; Select[Range[0, 200], q] (* _Amiram Eldar_, May 09 2026 *)
